1
00:00:00,106 --> 00:00:01,371
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:01,380 --> 00:00:02,947
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:02,965 --> 00:00:04,205
Hello, is this 911?

4
00:00:04,321 --> 00:00:06,625
This is Gold Pick Café. Someone's injured.

5
00:00:06,628 --> 00:00:07,973
Please come quickly!

6
00:00:07,997 --> 00:00:09,099
Are you okay?

7
00:00:09,423 --> 00:00:11,065
Ji Ni.

8
00:00:11,402 --> 00:00:12,481
Ji Ni!

9
00:00:14,596 --> 00:00:16,566
No, help this person first.

10
00:00:16,633 --> 00:00:18,157
My friend should be first!

11
00:00:22,416 --> 00:00:23,740
Wait.

12
00:00:24,129 --> 00:00:25,502
- My leg...
- I already called an ambulance.

13
00:00:25,523 --> 00:00:26,591
They'll be here soon.

14
00:00:34,321 --> 00:00:35,521
There's blood.

15
00:00:35,546 --> 00:00:37,068
You're bleeding from your head.

16
00:00:37,093 --> 00:00:39,106
Don't move. Stay still. I'll check.

17
00:00:42,703 --> 00:00:44,727
You're out of it.

18
00:00:44,752 --> 00:00:46,983
I told you not to get involved
in other people's business!

19
00:00:46,990 --> 00:00:49,183
Last time you intervened
in an abusive relationship,

20
00:00:49,214 --> 00:00:50,618
and you were the one who got hurt!

21
00:00:52,468 --> 00:00:53,877
Keep it down.

22
00:00:55,320 --> 00:00:58,408
Hey, you jerk... that married woman...

23
00:01:00,556 --> 00:01:01,690
What were you talking about?

24
00:01:01,714 --> 00:01:04,301
- I...
- How did you find out?

25
00:01:05,890 --> 00:01:07,797
Calling someone "jerk"
after she jumped in to help,

26
00:01:07,843 --> 00:01:09,082
that's a bit much.

27
00:01:09,107 --> 00:01:11,430
With that attitude,
no wonder you got beaten up.

28
00:01:12,032 --> 00:01:13,074
Not you.

29
00:01:14,290 --> 00:01:15,820
That Han Jeong Won is married,

30
00:01:16,069 --> 00:01:17,069
is that true?

31
00:01:17,596 --> 00:01:18,731
How did you find out?

32
00:01:18,951 --> 00:01:19,980
About that,

33
00:01:20,555 --> 00:01:22,832
she went to our school. I told her.

34
00:01:23,876 --> 00:01:27,285
This is her wedding photo.
She was really famous.

35
00:01:27,310 --> 00:01:29,194
She's like a queen bee
who dates both older and younger guys.

36
00:01:32,377 --> 00:01:33,642
The ambulance is here!

37
00:01:39,396 --> 00:01:41,931
Over here, his leg is injured.
He has a prosthetic leg.

38
00:01:45,343 --> 00:01:46,449
Please don't move.

39
00:01:46,651 --> 00:01:49,183
Please take me
to Second Orthopedic Clinic.

40
00:01:49,210 --> 00:01:50,800
I always get treated there.

41
00:01:50,824 --> 00:01:51,870
Okay.

42
00:01:54,589 --> 00:01:56,315
- His guardian, please get in.
- Yes.

43
00:01:59,890 --> 00:02:01,083
Do you know his family?

44
00:02:01,495 --> 00:02:03,264
- Contact them.
- Okay.

45
00:02:08,024 --> 00:02:10,024
(Ambulance Service)

46
00:02:10,877 --> 00:02:12,165
Do you know him?

47
00:02:12,664 --> 00:02:13,736
Who is he?

48
00:02:14,430 --> 00:02:16,648
You don't even remember Han Jeong Won,

49
00:02:16,650 --> 00:02:18,489
so how do you know the man she's with?

50
00:02:30,043 --> 00:02:31,093
You come here often.

51
00:02:31,117 --> 00:02:32,189
What's going on this time?

52
00:02:32,770 --> 00:02:34,215
Coming back from the academy?

53
00:02:36,910 --> 00:02:40,095
You'd probably be a great singing teacher.
You were always good.

54
00:02:41,078 --> 00:02:42,392
Did you come just to say something nice?

55
00:02:44,210 --> 00:02:45,721
You've changed a lot too.

56
00:02:46,030 --> 00:02:47,515
Your words have gotten pretty sharp.

57
00:02:47,937 --> 00:02:49,286
I learned it from you.

58
00:02:49,363 --> 00:02:50,912
Time just made me this way.

59
00:02:51,343 --> 00:02:52,959
You know now, don't you?

60
00:02:54,183 --> 00:02:56,766
You know nothing can be resolved
unless you give in.

61
00:02:57,050 --> 00:02:58,550
Same goes for his company shares.

62
00:02:58,649 --> 00:03:00,790
You must've realized by now
that those papers...

63
00:03:01,464 --> 00:03:02,787
aren't just scraps.

64
00:03:03,207 --> 00:03:04,340
Yeah, that's right.

65
00:03:04,523 --> 00:03:07,063
If I want to,
I can take everything from you.

66
00:03:07,103 --> 00:03:08,103
So...

67
00:03:08,699 --> 00:03:10,300
you want me and Ji Ni to move out?

68
00:03:10,709 --> 00:03:12,815
- Does it have to be that way?
- Why did you even come?

69
00:03:12,896 --> 00:03:14,527
- To negotiate?
- No.

70
00:03:14,799 --> 00:03:16,119
To beg.

71
00:03:21,163 --> 00:03:22,218
Yeong Ju...

72
00:03:23,931 --> 00:03:25,488
I was really wrong.

73
00:03:25,929 --> 00:03:27,422
I'm sorry for everything.

74
00:03:28,030 --> 00:03:31,387
Please let Ji Ni and me
keep living together.

75
00:03:31,429 --> 00:03:33,396
Would moving to a smaller place
really separate you two?

76
00:03:33,815 --> 00:03:35,479
Don't try to play on my sympathy.

77
00:03:35,556 --> 00:03:36,832
Yeong Ju.

78
00:03:37,836 --> 00:03:40,643
He really came with nothing.

79
00:03:40,667 --> 00:03:41,928
You know that.

80
00:03:41,970 --> 00:03:44,734
Min Ki and I bought that house together.

81
00:03:44,755 --> 00:03:46,495
Half of it is still under mortgage.

82
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:48,393
If you take what's left after that,

83
00:03:48,643 --> 00:03:50,933
Ji Ni and I will have nowhere to go.

84
00:03:51,036 --> 00:03:53,767
Please, I'm begging you.

85
00:03:59,932 --> 00:04:02,791
Yeong Ju, should I even get
on my knees and beg?

86
00:04:02,815 --> 00:04:05,440
- Yeong Ju.
- Enough. Don't make a scene.

87
00:04:05,450 --> 00:04:06,795
If you're done talking, go.

88
00:04:06,910 --> 00:04:08,268
If the kids come,
you'll run into them again.

89
00:04:08,841 --> 00:04:10,305
I'm begging you, Yeong Ju.

90
00:04:10,330 --> 00:04:12,334
You'll do it for me, right?

91
00:04:12,688 --> 00:04:14,155
Please, Yeong Ju.

92
00:04:34,096 --> 00:04:35,854
This is driving me crazy.

93
00:04:36,264 --> 00:04:37,414
Seriously...

94
00:04:37,498 --> 00:04:39,952
I'm so mad I could lose my mind.

95
00:04:46,441 --> 00:04:49,407
You bastard. Are you happy now?

96
00:04:49,549 --> 00:04:52,089
Are you happy leaving us in this mess?

97
00:04:54,132 --> 00:04:55,632
Damn it!

98
00:05:02,197 --> 00:05:03,463
(Na Ji Ni)

99
00:05:08,176 --> 00:05:09,176
Hello?

100
00:05:11,179 --> 00:05:12,179
Right now?

101
00:05:13,376 --> 00:05:14,415
Okay.

102
00:05:14,443 --> 00:05:15,443
And...

103
00:05:15,707 --> 00:05:18,497
they said he'll need crutches.
Take them with you.

104
00:05:18,551 --> 00:05:20,800
Okay.

105
00:05:28,316 --> 00:05:29,316
What?

106
00:05:29,541 --> 00:05:31,713
Are you shocked I'm not an only child?

107
00:05:32,570 --> 00:05:34,526
And you still threw yourself
in harm's way?

108
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:36,427
Even after they treated you so badly?

109
00:05:36,490 --> 00:05:38,740
That has nothing to do with it.

110
00:05:38,976 --> 00:05:41,615
I'd have done it
even for a stranger. You know that.

111
00:05:42,236 --> 00:05:43,236
Let alone...

112
00:05:44,523 --> 00:05:46,613
Don't look so shocked.
Your eyes will pop out.

113
00:05:46,870 --> 00:05:48,126
Didn't you notice?

114
00:05:48,536 --> 00:05:50,096
There were two funeral rooms too.

115
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,386
Really?

116
00:05:51,835 --> 00:05:53,099
How didn't I know?

117
00:05:53,262 --> 00:05:54,522
You came the day after
they combined the rooms.

118
00:05:54,554 --> 00:05:55,830
There were two on the first day.

119
00:05:57,663 --> 00:06:00,151
Stop being so surprised.
It's making me feel bad.

120
00:06:00,176 --> 00:06:02,713
I don't want you to be like the others.

121
00:06:03,134 --> 00:06:06,719
How did you keep all this inside
for so long?

122
00:06:06,743 --> 00:06:09,898
Exactly. That's why I just kept painting.

123
00:06:13,297 --> 00:06:14,671
What now?

124
00:06:20,427 --> 00:06:22,693
What? Which hospital?

125
00:06:22,717 --> 00:06:25,121
Don't go. His family will be there.

126
00:06:25,690 --> 00:06:27,396
The doctors will take care of him.

127
00:06:28,269 --> 00:06:30,806
But are you ready to meet his family?

128
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:31,993
Can you handle that?

129
00:06:32,076 --> 00:06:34,873
- So you're his awful sister, right?
- Yes.

130
00:06:35,197 --> 00:06:37,267
Having a sister like me
is hard enough on him,

131
00:06:37,269 --> 00:06:38,817
so end things here.

132
00:06:39,462 --> 00:06:42,388
You could face charges for that assault.
You know that, right?

133
00:06:42,412 --> 00:06:44,659
- Hey!
- Don't mess around.

134
00:06:45,481 --> 00:06:47,598
His life is hard enough.
Don't toy with him.

135
00:06:48,690 --> 00:06:50,444
Who says I'm playing with him?

136
00:06:50,850 --> 00:06:53,505
- Don't jump to conclusions.
- If you're serious, get divorced.

137
00:06:53,530 --> 00:06:54,746
Before everyone finds out.

138
00:06:55,690 --> 00:06:56,703
Can you do that?

139
00:06:56,727 --> 00:06:57,766
Aren't you overstepping?

140
00:06:57,790 --> 00:06:59,521
People dating before getting divorced...

141
00:06:59,523 --> 00:07:01,750
made my life miserable.

142
00:07:01,775 --> 00:07:05,719
Don't just call it love.
Get divorced before going to a hotel.

143
00:07:06,123 --> 00:07:08,862
That's cruel to your husband,

144
00:07:08,864 --> 00:07:09,975
and for Cha Seung Woo...

145
00:07:11,132 --> 00:07:12,806
to the director, it's deception.

146
00:07:12,830 --> 00:07:14,075
Right? It's deception.

147
00:07:14,130 --> 00:07:17,063
You're dragging someone
who hates affairs...

148
00:07:17,950 --> 00:07:19,567
into an affair. Isn't that cruel?

149
00:07:36,959 --> 00:07:38,685
How did you get hurt this badly?

150
00:07:39,983 --> 00:07:41,812
Use crutches for now.

151
00:07:41,909 --> 00:07:45,085
I prescribed antibiotics.
It's summer, so keep the wound clean.

152
00:07:46,596 --> 00:07:48,390
- Okay.
- Come back for follow-ups.

153
00:07:49,187 --> 00:07:50,817
- See you next time.
- Okay.

154
00:07:57,216 --> 00:08:01,016
You can go now. Thank you for everything.

155
00:08:01,041 --> 00:08:02,890
At least until your family gets here...

156
00:08:08,243 --> 00:08:09,243
Seung Hyun.

157
00:08:09,828 --> 00:08:12,541
Okay. I'll leave, then.

158
00:08:13,111 --> 00:08:14,321
I'll thank you properly later.

159
00:08:14,384 --> 00:08:15,384
Okay.

160
00:08:21,276 --> 00:08:22,476
What happened?

161
00:08:35,230 --> 00:08:37,057
I never asked you to marry me.

162
00:08:38,089 --> 00:08:39,232
What are you so upset about?

163
00:08:39,790 --> 00:08:41,250
We were just in love.

164
00:08:42,830 --> 00:08:43,838
Han Jeong Won.

165
00:08:43,863 --> 00:08:45,343
Everything you heard is true.

166
00:08:45,856 --> 00:08:47,921
It's true you got hurt because of me.

167
00:08:49,716 --> 00:08:50,826
How easy.

168
00:08:51,583 --> 00:08:53,209
So it was this simple.

169
00:08:53,986 --> 00:08:56,778
Well, depending on how you see it.

170
00:08:57,676 --> 00:08:58,730
Why?

171
00:09:00,070 --> 00:09:01,521
Why me?

172
00:09:02,831 --> 00:09:04,182
I was curious.

173
00:09:04,889 --> 00:09:08,007
I wanted to see what you're like in love.

174
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:12,415
You heard everything, right?

175
00:09:12,787 --> 00:09:14,280
That's the kind of woman I am.

176
00:09:14,305 --> 00:09:15,401
I don't believe in love.

177
00:09:15,456 --> 00:09:17,682
Fun, money, desire, necessity.

178
00:09:18,010 --> 00:09:19,898
Love is no different from any of them.

179
00:09:20,383 --> 00:09:22,432
I think people who believe
love is special...

180
00:09:23,078 --> 00:09:24,842
are all naive.

181
00:09:32,437 --> 00:09:33,684
Get your hand off me.

182
00:09:36,723 --> 00:09:38,300
Thanks for playing along.

183
00:09:38,953 --> 00:09:40,252
I had fun too.

184
00:09:43,570 --> 00:09:44,571
Fine!

185
00:09:45,169 --> 00:09:47,221
Every time we met,
you talked about marriage,

186
00:09:47,785 --> 00:09:49,427
and I didn't know how to end things,

187
00:09:50,744 --> 00:09:52,327
but that solved it.

188
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:55,515
This is better, right?

189
00:10:20,469 --> 00:10:22,990
I can hear you cursing me out.

190
00:10:23,207 --> 00:10:24,667
As long as you know.

191
00:10:24,769 --> 00:10:27,062
Like father, like son, right?

192
00:10:27,350 --> 00:10:29,862
I guess this is payback
for all the cursing I've done.

193
00:10:29,887 --> 00:10:31,821
I told you not to say
"Like father, like son."

194
00:10:32,423 --> 00:10:35,710
- Shut up before I smack you.
- To mom...

195
00:10:35,735 --> 00:10:36,963
Don't let her notice anything.

196
00:10:36,988 --> 00:10:38,298
She'd have a heart attack.

197
00:10:39,969 --> 00:10:41,148
I could just die.

198
00:10:41,172 --> 00:10:42,172
Hey!

199
00:10:42,670 --> 00:10:45,343
How can you still not get it?
What's wrong with you?

200
00:10:45,404 --> 00:10:46,837
You thought...

201
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:49,115
Mai was just a poor student
trying to make ends meet.

202
00:10:50,074 --> 00:10:51,363
Yeah, go ahead and hit me.

203
00:10:51,388 --> 00:10:52,516
You do it.

204
00:10:52,917 --> 00:10:54,486
I should've let them hit me more.

205
00:10:56,321 --> 00:10:57,382
Just you wait.

206
00:11:12,456 --> 00:11:14,421
What happened?

207
00:11:14,691 --> 00:11:16,072
How did you get hurt?

208
00:11:16,097 --> 00:11:18,830
I tried not to get hurt
so I wouldn't make you worry,

209
00:11:19,159 --> 00:11:20,331
but I'm sorry.

210
00:11:20,356 --> 00:11:22,391
At least your mouth's okay.

211
00:11:22,415 --> 00:11:23,495
Mai,

212
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:25,075
I don't need dinner.

213
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:26,596
You need to eat
before taking your medicine.

214
00:11:27,209 --> 00:11:29,759
Right, the medicine.

215
00:11:30,589 --> 00:11:31,596
I'm sorry, Mai.

216
00:11:31,621 --> 00:11:33,536
Okay, I'll fix you something to eat.

217
00:11:34,815 --> 00:11:36,190
I should check on O Reum.

218
00:11:36,215 --> 00:11:37,581
Is his cold any better?

219
00:11:37,691 --> 00:11:39,005
O Reum, it's Uncle!

220
00:12:07,710 --> 00:12:09,167
I was curious.

221
00:12:09,255 --> 00:12:12,280
I wanted to see what you're like in love.

222
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,007
Seung Woo, come out!

223
00:12:24,496 --> 00:12:26,087
Go help him.

224
00:12:26,187 --> 00:12:27,453
Help him with what?

225
00:12:27,478 --> 00:12:28,832
He can come out on his own.

226
00:12:30,273 --> 00:12:31,468
Seung Woo.

227
00:12:31,493 --> 00:12:33,055
Mom, don't come in.

228
00:12:33,158 --> 00:12:34,590
I'll come out.

229
00:12:43,156 --> 00:12:44,156
Mom.

230
00:12:45,523 --> 00:12:46,921
Are you really okay?

231
00:12:47,110 --> 00:12:48,430
You don't need to go to the hospital?

232
00:12:50,241 --> 00:12:53,581
You really are fearless, aren't you?

233
00:12:53,916 --> 00:12:56,718
What if you had a scar on your face?

234
00:12:56,969 --> 00:13:00,750
If your dad found out,
he would've gone crazy.

235
00:13:00,902 --> 00:13:04,071
If dad knew what happened yesterday,
he would've said I did the right thing.

236
00:13:04,095 --> 00:13:06,646
- What?
- Dad's a good person.

237
00:13:07,346 --> 00:13:08,948
- What about me?
- You're...

238
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:11,525
an even better woman
whom a good man chose.

239
00:13:12,115 --> 00:13:13,309
Listen to you.

240
00:13:13,735 --> 00:13:14,992
Listen to you.

241
00:13:19,270 --> 00:13:20,477
What are you doing today?

242
00:13:23,350 --> 00:13:26,075
I'll apply for the audition
and sort out your dad's company.

243
00:13:26,322 --> 00:13:27,394
We...

244
00:13:28,225 --> 00:13:30,149
don't have to worry about the house
anymore, right?

245
00:13:30,174 --> 00:13:32,557
We have to split the company shares.

246
00:13:32,837 --> 00:13:36,941
I can't believe we have to split it
with those people who did nothing.

247
00:13:36,989 --> 00:13:38,254
Honestly, I'm...

248
00:13:38,279 --> 00:13:40,663
meditating just to keep my temper.

249
00:13:55,999 --> 00:13:57,999
(CEO Cha Min Ki)

250
00:14:07,356 --> 00:14:08,369
Director.

251
00:14:08,413 --> 00:14:09,554
Hello.

252
00:14:10,004 --> 00:14:12,090
I've been busy dealing with things.
I'm sorry it took me so long to visit.

253
00:14:12,114 --> 00:14:13,150
I suppose so.

254
00:14:13,214 --> 00:14:14,232
Please have a seat.

255
00:14:20,450 --> 00:14:22,176
The projects that were in progress...

256
00:14:22,185 --> 00:14:25,249
were all wrapped up or put on hold
when the CEO was hospitalized.

257
00:14:25,296 --> 00:14:27,438
I think he expected he might die.

258
00:14:28,132 --> 00:14:30,167
- I suppose so.
- What about the legal matters?

259
00:14:30,169 --> 00:14:31,789
They're still being processed.

260
00:14:32,616 --> 00:14:35,417
Can I take over as CEO for now?

261
00:14:35,419 --> 00:14:37,184
If everyone agrees, there's no problem.

262
00:14:38,072 --> 00:14:39,207
That damn agreement...

263
00:14:39,674 --> 00:14:40,698
Sorry?

264
00:14:41,479 --> 00:14:43,223
Nothing.

265
00:14:43,430 --> 00:14:44,854
What's this?

266
00:14:45,656 --> 00:14:47,693
He left the overseas
investment deal untouched.

267
00:14:47,695 --> 00:14:49,529
It's a highly lucrative contract.

268
00:14:50,579 --> 00:14:51,901
(Overseas content joint investment
and profit-sharing agreement)

269
00:14:51,903 --> 00:14:54,010
I can't really tell
just by looking at this.

270
00:14:54,430 --> 00:14:57,348
I'll find someone to consult.

271
00:14:57,350 --> 00:14:58,721
Please share your opinion too.

272
00:14:58,723 --> 00:15:01,404
I think CEO Cha kept this deal...

273
00:15:01,406 --> 00:15:04,494
to support you and Ms. Ji Ni.

274
00:15:04,496 --> 00:15:06,990
I'd recommend keeping it as is.

275
00:15:07,830 --> 00:15:11,449
- Okay, I understand.
- Okay then.

276
00:15:20,183 --> 00:15:22,109
What's the point of preparing all this...

277
00:15:23,003 --> 00:15:26,065
when those two shameless brats
are trying to get their hands on it?

278
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:31,949
My legs...

279
00:15:36,963 --> 00:15:39,511
When my legs swell, it's hard to move.

280
00:15:39,896 --> 00:15:41,346
I'll clean it up before I leave.

281
00:15:42,776 --> 00:15:45,080
Why isn't Ji Hu coming?

282
00:15:48,903 --> 00:15:50,052
Excuse me...

283
00:15:50,933 --> 00:15:52,116
Ma'am.

284
00:15:55,921 --> 00:15:58,213
You're here to apply for
the cellist position, right?

285
00:16:02,670 --> 00:16:04,052
You accept paper applications too, right?

286
00:16:04,252 --> 00:16:06,901
Yes, of course.
Many people bring them in person.

287
00:16:06,903 --> 00:16:09,601
I was passing by, so I stopped in.

288
00:16:09,603 --> 00:16:12,243
- I already sent the music file.
- You're Na Se Ri, right?

289
00:16:12,550 --> 00:16:14,054
I'm a huge fan.

290
00:16:14,580 --> 00:16:15,804
Thank you.

291
00:16:15,806 --> 00:16:17,721
Ma'am, didn't you work at KBC?

292
00:16:18,363 --> 00:16:20,668
Then why are you here?

293
00:16:22,055 --> 00:16:23,063
Who are you?

294
00:16:23,563 --> 00:16:25,556
Why do you keep acting like you know me?

295
00:16:26,790 --> 00:16:28,021
Then I'll get going.

296
00:16:28,214 --> 00:16:29,809
Yes, we'll contact you.

297
00:16:33,063 --> 00:16:34,088
Ma'am!

298
00:16:34,780 --> 00:16:37,338
Who are you calling "ma'am"?
Stop calling me that.

299
00:16:38,138 --> 00:16:39,832
Did you really get kicked out?

300
00:16:40,605 --> 00:16:44,921
See? Korea's a conservative society.

301
00:16:46,243 --> 00:16:48,487
Ma'am, go to Europe.

302
00:16:48,489 --> 00:16:49,816
Over there, nobody cares.

303
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:55,546
Why? Are you annoyed all of a sudden?

304
00:16:58,538 --> 00:16:59,588
What a bitch.

305
00:16:59,936 --> 00:17:02,988
Ma'am, how could you say that...

306
00:17:05,623 --> 00:17:07,914
Hey! What are you doing?

307
00:17:07,916 --> 00:17:10,208
This is what my husband wanted to do.

308
00:17:10,210 --> 00:17:12,616
This is payback for what you did to Ji Ni!

309
00:17:13,883 --> 00:17:15,610
If you want to report me, go ahead.

310
00:17:15,620 --> 00:17:18,888
I'll pay the fine or do the time!

311
00:17:20,061 --> 00:17:21,136
You horrible bitch!

312
00:17:21,537 --> 00:17:23,067
You'll get what's coming to you!

313
00:17:23,662 --> 00:17:24,869
Painting?

314
00:17:24,969 --> 00:17:27,692
With that attitude,
you'll never be a good painter!

315
00:17:27,694 --> 00:17:30,520
- Ma'am, are you crazy?
- You're the crazy one!

316
00:17:30,522 --> 00:17:32,521
How dare you come to a funeral
and say something like that?

317
00:17:32,773 --> 00:17:34,784
Asking if I'd been promoted
to the legal wife?

318
00:17:35,583 --> 00:17:38,569
I'm going to rip that mouth
of yours apart today.

319
00:17:38,896 --> 00:17:41,314
You think I avoided you
because I was scared?

320
00:17:41,317 --> 00:17:43,501
I held back because of Ji Ni!

321
00:17:43,503 --> 00:17:45,079
What's so important about a name?

322
00:17:45,081 --> 00:17:48,198
I was afraid of disgrace and rumors!

323
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,738
I regret it so much!

324
00:17:50,114 --> 00:17:52,004
Because of a bitch like you...

325
00:17:52,006 --> 00:17:55,861
I didn't even realize my daughter
was being called "a child of sin!"

326
00:17:56,696 --> 00:17:59,594
I'm not holding back anymore. Sue me!

327
00:17:59,603 --> 00:18:02,196
Doesn't your father work
under his own name?

328
00:18:02,596 --> 00:18:07,261
I don't need anything anymore!
Go on, try it!

329
00:18:07,264 --> 00:18:08,527
Do Hee!

330
00:18:08,529 --> 00:18:10,324
Ji Hu!

331
00:18:12,721 --> 00:18:13,909
What's going on?

332
00:18:14,269 --> 00:18:16,895
If you're curious, ask this bitch.

333
00:18:18,969 --> 00:18:21,554
Ji Hu, this woman came to audition
for the cello ensemble.

334
00:18:21,556 --> 00:18:22,830
Don't let her pass the audition.

335
00:18:25,850 --> 00:18:27,198
What now?

336
00:18:32,489 --> 00:18:33,875
Where's my résumé?

337
00:18:42,043 --> 00:18:45,163
Make sure you sue me. I'll be waiting.

338
00:18:45,630 --> 00:18:48,950
I will make you pay for what you did
to my daughter.

339
00:18:49,864 --> 00:18:52,462
Trusting the judgment of a director
who sides with people like this,

340
00:18:52,464 --> 00:18:54,588
I don't think I can perform here.

341
00:18:54,823 --> 00:18:56,398
My music is too good for this place.

342
00:18:59,610 --> 00:19:02,384
That woman must've lost her mind
after her husband died.

343
00:19:08,616 --> 00:19:09,940
Is she Na Ji Ni's mother?

344
00:19:10,442 --> 00:19:11,442
But why?

345
00:19:11,721 --> 00:19:14,525
- She bullied you at school, right?
- Exactly.

346
00:19:15,090 --> 00:19:16,510
That makes no sense.

347
00:19:16,583 --> 00:19:18,790
What did she mean by making you pay
for what you did to her daughter?

348
00:19:18,810 --> 00:19:21,704
That's my point.
She's sorry for what Ji Ni did to me.

349
00:19:23,590 --> 00:19:26,317
You don't understand.
That woman has the wrong idea.

350
00:19:27,744 --> 00:19:29,143
It's really unfair.

351
00:19:34,716 --> 00:19:35,744
Really?

352
00:19:37,932 --> 00:19:40,290
That made up for ten years of frustration.

353
00:19:41,438 --> 00:19:43,920
That was unnecessary.
What if she presses charges?

354
00:19:43,923 --> 00:19:46,107
Let her. That's why I hit her.

355
00:19:46,109 --> 00:19:48,127
Mom, you don't like rumors.

356
00:19:48,303 --> 00:19:50,230
That's why I regret it.

357
00:19:50,556 --> 00:19:52,952
If I hadn't lived in the shadows,
you wouldn't have suffered...

358
00:19:54,856 --> 00:19:56,221
That's all in the past.

359
00:19:56,223 --> 00:19:58,800
But are you really applying
to the Art and Culture Center?

360
00:19:58,802 --> 00:20:00,950
I told you, I ripped up my résumé.
How could I apply?

361
00:20:02,155 --> 00:20:04,150
Her boyfriend seemed decent enough.

362
00:20:04,393 --> 00:20:06,251
His eyes looked lifeless, though.

363
00:20:06,383 --> 00:20:09,856
Knowing Do Hee,
I doubt they'll live happily.

364
00:20:09,858 --> 00:20:12,396
Lifeless eyes? Jung A said that too.

365
00:20:12,676 --> 00:20:14,849
You and Jung A really do think alike.

366
00:20:15,410 --> 00:20:16,943
I really like Jung A.

367
00:20:19,069 --> 00:20:23,927
They say your dad's investment
in that foreign drama was lucrative.

368
00:20:24,016 --> 00:20:26,541
He did it for you and me...

369
00:20:27,490 --> 00:20:30,054
but now it'll only benefit
some other jerks.

370
00:20:35,968 --> 00:20:37,750
- Have a seat.
- Would you like coffee?

371
00:20:37,836 --> 00:20:39,956
- No, just water.
- Okay.

372
00:20:40,536 --> 00:20:43,356
Someone who spends 120,000 dollars a day
is asking for water?

373
00:20:44,056 --> 00:20:46,443
Get him fresh fruit juice.
The most expensive one.

374
00:20:49,563 --> 00:20:53,755
Thanks for what you did
for Seung Woo that day.

375
00:20:54,190 --> 00:20:56,576
- How's your wound?
- It's fine.

376
00:20:57,384 --> 00:20:58,636
My mom doesn't know.

377
00:21:05,350 --> 00:21:06,350
What is it?

378
00:21:06,975 --> 00:21:08,509
It's just...

379
00:21:11,089 --> 00:21:12,703
Take a look at this.

380
00:21:13,687 --> 00:21:18,058
Yeong Ju and I settled the house matter.
This is the company share agreement.

381
00:21:18,529 --> 00:21:21,863
Seung Woo will keep working
at the broadcasting station, right?

382
00:21:22,449 --> 00:21:25,367
He should do something
to deserve those shares.

383
00:21:25,369 --> 00:21:29,146
I started it, and I'll do all the work,
while he just takes the shares?

384
00:21:29,148 --> 00:21:30,968
That's pretty shameless, right?

385
00:21:30,970 --> 00:21:33,561
- He needs to work at the station.
- I need to perform too.

386
00:21:33,563 --> 00:21:35,436
- Then sell it.
- That's easy to say.

387
00:21:36,583 --> 00:21:39,515
Read it through carefully,
so you don't regret it.

388
00:21:40,005 --> 00:21:41,005
Okay.

389
00:21:49,943 --> 00:21:51,442
This breaks my heart.

390
00:21:51,868 --> 00:21:53,702
I'll try giving him the medicine.
Prepare another dose.

391
00:21:54,583 --> 00:21:58,636
O Reum, come play with Grandma.
Come here.

392
00:21:58,736 --> 00:22:00,790
My sweet boy.

393
00:22:01,856 --> 00:22:05,140
He isn't playing at all and looks so weak.

394
00:22:05,301 --> 00:22:07,630
This cold must be pretty bad.

395
00:22:07,970 --> 00:22:09,241
- Mother.
- Yes?

396
00:22:09,243 --> 00:22:10,244
Here.

397
00:22:10,246 --> 00:22:13,781
Take your medicine, O Reum,
so you'll get better soon.

398
00:22:13,783 --> 00:22:17,951
Get well soon so we can play
and go to daycare.

399
00:22:17,953 --> 00:22:19,658
Open wide.

400
00:22:19,959 --> 00:22:21,017
Come on.

401
00:22:22,011 --> 00:22:24,116
What do we do?

402
00:22:25,223 --> 00:22:27,850
Let's try again after he gets some sleep.

403
00:22:28,250 --> 00:22:29,594
His fever has gone down.

404
00:22:30,595 --> 00:22:33,405
What should we do?
He's never been this sick.

405
00:22:33,408 --> 00:22:34,862
Don't worry.

406
00:22:35,094 --> 00:22:37,905
He'll have another growth spurt
once he gets over this.

407
00:22:39,056 --> 00:22:42,930
He must be getting ready
to charm us even more.

408
00:22:45,283 --> 00:22:47,230
- Come here.
- Why?

409
00:22:47,603 --> 00:22:49,757
What did Seung Hyun mean earlier?

410
00:22:50,767 --> 00:22:53,134
I said it was nothing.
Why do you keep asking?

411
00:22:53,137 --> 00:22:54,742
Because you're hiding something.

412
00:22:55,284 --> 00:22:57,212
Is it related to how you got hurt?

413
00:22:57,214 --> 00:22:59,038
Mom, you don't need to know.

414
00:22:59,709 --> 00:23:01,419
I have another daughter, you know.

415
00:23:01,923 --> 00:23:04,568
- I can just ask Jung A.
- Mom.

416
00:23:04,570 --> 00:23:06,815
Have you ever won against me?
Tell me. Now.

417
00:23:13,283 --> 00:23:15,616
Is someone else's misery
that funny to you?

418
00:23:17,563 --> 00:23:21,596
He attacked his own father so viciously.

419
00:23:22,681 --> 00:23:25,234
Serves him right. That's hilarious.

420
00:23:26,050 --> 00:23:27,663
Does Yeong Ju know?

421
00:23:28,710 --> 00:23:29,763
Not yet?

422
00:23:30,270 --> 00:23:32,373
- Should I tell her?
- Mom,

423
00:23:32,375 --> 00:23:37,314
- if you actually do that...
- How scary. I won't.

424
00:23:37,316 --> 00:23:39,250
As if it'll stay buried
because I keep quiet.

425
00:23:39,376 --> 00:23:40,974
Why should I play the villain?

426
00:23:40,976 --> 00:23:43,416
I'll watch her cry
when she finds out later.

427
00:23:44,029 --> 00:23:47,707
He got so full of himself
after becoming a director.

428
00:23:49,796 --> 00:23:51,634
Live quietly for once.

429
00:23:57,250 --> 00:23:59,394
Do you think I act this way for no reason?

430
00:23:59,396 --> 00:24:01,047
I'm like this because I've been hurt too.

431
00:24:01,056 --> 00:24:05,063
When you couldn't go to high school,
people talked about you so much.

432
00:24:07,416 --> 00:24:08,763
Let's not talk about it.

433
00:24:10,396 --> 00:24:13,590
People with children shouldn't talk
about other people's children.

434
00:24:29,221 --> 00:24:30,629
How did you find out?

435
00:24:30,739 --> 00:24:32,746
Didn't you see the post
on the company intranet?

436
00:24:32,894 --> 00:24:34,373
The CEO knows too.

437
00:24:36,047 --> 00:24:37,067
I'm sorry.

438
00:24:37,069 --> 00:24:40,401
Your teammates said they didn't know
you two were dating.

439
00:24:40,403 --> 00:24:41,963
She said she wanted to keep it secret,

440
00:24:42,223 --> 00:24:44,773
so I thought she was worried
about dating someone at work.

441
00:24:45,103 --> 00:24:46,498
I only found out recently too.

442
00:24:47,424 --> 00:24:49,271
Where is she now?

443
00:24:49,273 --> 00:24:50,944
Writer Han disappeared.

444
00:24:51,403 --> 00:24:52,676
She submitted her resignation by email.

445
00:24:54,103 --> 00:24:56,531
From now on, I'll focus more on work...

446
00:24:56,533 --> 00:24:59,109
Enough. Take some time off for now.

447
00:24:59,136 --> 00:25:01,953
Use your unused vacation days
and take a trip somewhere.

448
00:25:01,955 --> 00:25:04,787
Station Director,
I'm currently preparing the program.

449
00:25:04,789 --> 00:25:06,748
Hand it over to someone else.

450
00:25:08,001 --> 00:25:09,623
Buy yourself some time.

451
00:25:10,450 --> 00:25:13,452
Director Cha ended up
leaving the company too.

452
00:25:13,454 --> 00:25:14,988
I wasn't having an affair.

453
00:25:15,178 --> 00:25:17,363
- This is different from what my dad did.
- What's different?

454
00:25:17,923 --> 00:25:21,457
Do you think you can avoid
being called just like him?

455
00:25:29,978 --> 00:25:32,230
What? Why are you home so early?

456
00:25:32,656 --> 00:25:33,804
I thought you had a lot of meetings.

457
00:25:35,763 --> 00:25:37,557
My schedule got pushed back.

458
00:25:38,998 --> 00:25:40,443
That's good.

459
00:25:40,610 --> 00:25:42,302
Rest until your leg fully heals.

460
00:25:45,103 --> 00:25:48,007
But why do you look so down?

461
00:25:48,890 --> 00:25:50,544
Want me to make you some cold noodles?

462
00:26:01,389 --> 00:26:04,701
- Mother.
- How's O Reum?

463
00:26:04,743 --> 00:26:06,550
They said to keep watching him.

464
00:26:07,083 --> 00:26:10,549
- But they did a blood test.
- A blood test?

465
00:26:10,777 --> 00:26:13,549
Why? Isn't it just a cold?

466
00:26:13,630 --> 00:26:16,230
I don't know. They said we'll see
when the results come out.

467
00:26:17,576 --> 00:26:20,549
He kept whining, but he's calmed down now.

468
00:26:25,430 --> 00:26:27,751
Is Cha Seung Woo here?

469
00:26:28,332 --> 00:26:31,836
- Yes. How can I help you?
- It's registered mail from the court.

470
00:26:31,870 --> 00:26:34,676
- What is your relationship to him?
- I'm his mother.

471
00:26:37,143 --> 00:26:39,150
- Please sign here.
- Okay.

472
00:26:46,705 --> 00:26:48,752
(Seoul Central District Court,
To Cha Seung Woo)

473
00:26:52,135 --> 00:26:55,149
(Complaint, Plaintiff Kim Hui Jun,
Defendant Cha Seung Woo)

474
00:26:56,256 --> 00:26:57,529
An affair partner?

475
00:26:58,530 --> 00:26:59,856
I'm home.

476
00:27:02,050 --> 00:27:03,069
Mom.

477
00:27:05,370 --> 00:27:06,752
What does this mean?

478
00:27:07,067 --> 00:27:09,414
Is Seung Woo being accused
of having an affair?

479
00:27:09,416 --> 00:27:12,930
You said he was going to marry someone.
Was she married?

480
00:27:14,568 --> 00:27:16,636
- Well...
- Did you know?

481
00:27:17,263 --> 00:27:20,156
Was he really having an affair?

482
00:27:20,302 --> 00:27:21,302
Mom...

483
00:27:22,301 --> 00:27:23,771
Mom, he didn't know.

484
00:27:23,773 --> 00:27:25,146
I think she deceived him.

485
00:27:25,410 --> 00:27:26,455
My goodness!

486
00:27:27,316 --> 00:27:28,650
Does that even make sense?

487
00:27:31,083 --> 00:27:32,589
Mom, are you okay?

488
00:27:34,903 --> 00:27:36,250
Where did he go?

489
00:27:36,576 --> 00:27:37,775
Where did that fool go?

490
00:27:38,276 --> 00:27:39,950
Call him. Hurry. Right now.

491
00:27:40,256 --> 00:27:42,043
He's with that woman, right?

492
00:27:42,444 --> 00:27:43,473
No, he's not.

493
00:27:43,687 --> 00:27:45,156
Find him. Hurry.

494
00:27:45,589 --> 00:27:48,649
How could this happen?
He's being sued over an affair!

495
00:27:48,703 --> 00:27:51,132
What's going to happen to his life now?

496
00:27:51,346 --> 00:27:52,741
Who is the woman?

497
00:27:53,509 --> 00:27:54,843
I'll meet her.

498
00:27:54,896 --> 00:27:57,273
- Who's this crazy woman?
- They broke up.

499
00:27:57,501 --> 00:28:00,049
- It's over.
- Then why is he being sued?

500
00:28:00,430 --> 00:28:01,996
Find him. Hurry.

501
00:28:02,623 --> 00:28:04,096
Call that crazy woman too.

502
00:28:04,334 --> 00:28:06,943
I'll kill her. Hurry!

503
00:28:24,233 --> 00:28:27,360
(Family Register)

504
00:28:27,463 --> 00:28:30,147
I hope she gets divorced and comes to me.

505
00:28:30,149 --> 00:28:31,475
I really did love her.

506
00:28:31,477 --> 00:28:33,910
Is your son's affair harder to deal with
than your husband's?

507
00:28:33,912 --> 00:28:36,021
You still haven't broken up with her?
You still haven't come to your senses.

508
00:28:36,023 --> 00:28:38,154
Don't insult her! She's the woman I loved.

509
00:28:38,156 --> 00:28:40,872
I'm sorry. Please forgive me
just this once. I'm begging you.

510
00:28:40,874 --> 00:28:42,608
I heard you're dating Do Hee.

511
00:28:42,610 --> 00:28:45,254
I wanted to hear directly from you
what you meant when you said...

512
00:28:45,481 --> 00:28:46,905
you'd make her pay
for what she did to Ji Ni.

513
00:28:49,589 --> 00:28:51,589
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
